ex.html UEFA.com]; official website\n\n{{UEFA Women's U-19 Championship}}\n\n[[Category:2012 UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship|1]]\n[[Category:UEFA Women's Under-19 Championship qualification|2012 first]]\n[[Category:2011 in women's association football|UEFA]]\n[[Category:2012 in youth sport]]\n", "text_old": "'''2012 UEFA Women's U-19 Championship First Qualifying Round''' was the first round of qualifications for the Final Tournament of [[2012 UEFA Women's U-19 Championship]]. They were played in September 2011. 40 teams were split into 10 groups of 4 and teams in each group played each other once. [[Turkey women's national football team|Turkey]] received a bye to the final as host. The top two teams in each group and the best third-placed team entered the [[2012 UEFA Women's U-19 Championship Second qualifying round]] to join [[England women's national football team|England]], [[France women's national football team|France]] and [[Germany women's national football team|Germany]].\n\nThe host of each mini tournament is listed in ''italics''.\n\n==Groups==\nThe draw was made on 16 November 2010 at UEFA headquarters in Nyon.<ref>{{cite web|title=2012 Women's U19 qualifying draw|url=http://www.uefa.com/womensunder19/news/newsid=1563399.html|publisher=UEFA|accessdate=9 June 2011|date=16 November 2010}}</ref>\n\n=== Group 1 ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n!width=180|Team\n!width=20|Pld\n!width=20|W\n!width=20|D\n!width=20|L\n!width=20|GF\n!width=20|GA\n!width=20|GD\n!width=20|Pts\n|- bgcolor=ccffcc\n|align=\"left\"|{{fbwu|19|NOR}}\n|3||3||0||0||20||3||+17||'''9'''\n|- bgcolor=ccffcc\n|align=\"left\"|{{fbwu|19|NED}}\n|3||2||0||1||10||5||+5||'''6'''\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|{{fbwu|19|CRO}}\n|3||1||0||2||3||12||\u22129||'''3'''\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|''{{fbwu|19|BUL}}''\n|3||0||0||3||0||13||\u221213||'''0'''\n|}\n<ref>[http://en.archive.uefa.com/competitions/wunder19/history/season=2012/round=2000219/group=2001264.html First Round \u2013 Group 1 Results]{{Dead link|date=September 2019 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\n{{football box\n|date = 17 September 2011\n|time = 16:00\n|team1 = {{fbwu-rt|19|NOR}}\n|score = 9\u20130\n|team2 = {{fbwu|19|BUL}}\n|report = [http://www.uefa.com/womensunder19/season=2012/matches/round=2000219/match=2003511/index.html Report]\n|goals1 = [[Caroline Graham Hansen|Hansen]] {{goal|13||62}}<br />Knudsen {{goal|19}}<br />[[Ada Hegerberg|Hegerberg]] {{goal|31||73}}<br />[[Guro Reiten|Reiten]] {{goal|54||55||70||74}} \n|goals2 = \n|stadium = [[Georgi Benkovski Stadium]], [[Pazardzhik]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = Leen Martens ([[Royal Belgian Football Association|Belgium]])\n}}\n----\n{{football box\n|date = 17 September 2011\n|time = 16:00\n|team1 = {{fbwu-rt|19|NED}}\n|score = 5\u20131\n|team2 = {{fbwu|19|CRO}}\n|report = [http://www.uefa.com/womensunder19/season=2012/matches/round=2000219/match=2003512/index.html Report]\n|goals1 = [[Eshly Bakker|Bakker]] {{goal|9||52||65||73}}<br />[[Judith Westervelt|Westervelt]] {{goal|37}}\n|goals2 = [[Martina \u0160alek|\u0160alek]] {{goal|43}}\n|stadium = [[Lokomotiv Stadium (Mezdra)|Lokomotiv Stadium]], [[Mezdra]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = Ginta P\u0113ce ([[Latvian Football Federation|Latvia]])\n}}\n----\n{{football box\n|date = 19 September 2011\n|time = 16:00\n|team1 = {{fbwu-rt|19|NOR}}\n|score = 7\u20131\n|team2 = {{fbwu|19|CRO}}\n|report = [http://www.uefa.com/womensunder19/season=2012/matches/round=2000219/match=2003533/index.html Report]\n|goals1 = [[Mia Marie Voltervik|Voltervik]] {{goal|12}}<br />[[Martine Berget|Berget]] {{goal|16}}<br />[[Ada Hegerberg|Hegerberg]] {{goal|34|pen.|75}}<br />[[Marit Sandtr\u00f8en|Sandtr\u00f8en]] {{goal|82}}<br />[[Anne Marthe Birkeland|Birkeland]] {{goal|85}}\n|goals2 = [[Antonija Kotarac|Kotarac]] {{goal|70}}\n|stadium = [[Georgi Benkovski Stadium]], [[Pazardzhik]]\n|attendance =\n|referee = Ginta P\u0113ce ([[Latvian Football Federation|Latvia]])\n}}\n----\n{{football box\n|